<br>
First will be the hard part.  Where will we stand?<br>
<br>
My opinion is that we will be in worse shape the both Blademasters and Mercenaries after the patch.  We got none of the light tank changes for the better (enhanced bleed effect and increased side positional as we have no left axe side positional and all our main styles are behind which just got its area reduced).  We have no access to the fluff enhancements such as flurry.  No shield spec to get engage to help us vs. archers who will be very beefed up with this patch and Bladeturn will be of much less help to us.  We may still do slightly more damage then our light tank counterparts, but a lot of that is from our 100% haste effect vs. theres whenever both weapons swing and that we normally use a slow right hand to increase damage.  But does that balance out losing even the 150-200pt once a battle flurry?  It remains to be seen.<br>
<br>
Our class defining ability, frenzy, now has a nullification in the blademaster abiliy and the mercenary ability.  They are on longer durations with no backdraws.  Where as we lose parry, evade and half our AF to get criticals on every swing for 20 seconds from 1 to 99%.  If the range had even been shortened it may have helped some there.<br>
<br>
So what do we need then?<br>
<br>
1) Access to all the current changes they gave BMs and Mercs: Bleed enhancements, flurry, etc<br>
<br>
2) Shorten the range of criticals from 1 to 99 to 35 - 70 making it a viable ability vs. increased parry/block in RvR, BM/Merc abilities cancel it out, BOF makes it pointless, etc.<br>
<br>
3) Remove penalties from Frenzy or give us an additional boost outside the criticals.  We have no defense during that time and the entire ability can be nullified by too many things while still leaving us with no defense.<br>
<br>
4) Increase Left Axe skill line to enhance another ability such as evade inreases by a small amount for every spec pt in left axe.  At the moment, its in the same boat as both Cd/Dw where main weapon skills do equal or better damage which is wrong for any of the advanced specs but Zerks have no other way to spec and Left Axe is much less viable at low spec then Cd/Dw. <br>
(Example for the above statement: A BM or Merc CAN spec shield, weapon and leave DW low to be a more defensive tank.  If they are not the one holding aggro during a fight, there shield does them no good, so even a 1 in DW/CD allows them a chance to swing for 100% damage. A 1 left axe leaves a zerk doing less damage over time then if they had just used a 2hander.)<br>
<br>
5) Lack of utility or role of a berserker needs to be addressed.  With the current level of there damage abilities, they bring nothing to a group other then a chance to do semi-decent damage every 7 minutes at a substantial cost to themselves and then there group.  A warrior, the most vanilla of all classes, brings more to the group with higher base damage (patch increase), high shield skill for defense and anytime stun not effected by resists or determination, access to 2handers for damage equal to or greater then zerks and with mastery of pain can do crits nearly as often as zerks without the penalties. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=gorsteir>Gorsteir</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#000000>(6/4/03 2:28 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=104.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where do we go from 1.62?</span><hr size=1> I was a little mad at first that DFrost was nerfed but Mythics explanation was ok i think, what we must do is utilize our positional styles. I think this makes the beserker more challenging, than just DFrosting all the time. It can be a bit hard with a high aug healer in the group <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  because of lag.<br>
