[quote]This is why the primary combat style chains for these light tanks are positional in nature - they assume that someone else is holding a monster or enemy player's aggression.[/quote]<br>
and I look at at style and I only see one positional chain ( from behind) no side no front not even a style for those position, we only have chain on evade and evade. if we are not to be the main tank ( pve or rvr) how are we supposed to do those chains and do the damages we are supposed to do? for this  I totally agree with you points number 3 and 5<br>
<br>
My understanding for our short timer on rage was that we had limitation if every one else is on a 7 min timer, I  don't see  the point for this beside mythological references.  as for crits  I would prefer 30-70 ( I really hate when I crit for 10% and people hates when we crit for 90% so that should makes every one happy and makes it easier to pass the vendo without defense loss)<br>
<br>
for the cosmetic changes I would like to see a vendo ( or  other model) proportional to the size of the toon ( as a dwarf i hate becoming bigger than troll) <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#c0c0c0><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub79.ezboard.com/blighttanksofdaoc.showUserPublicProfile?gid=shadowzerkers>shadowzerkers</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Initiate</span><br>  Posts: 5<br> <font color=#000000>(6/10/03 5:10 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=104.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Where do we go from 1.62?</span><hr size=1>  You can post all the damage numbers you want but you dont know how badly it is till you have seen it for yourself. I play a lvl 50 zerker on iseuld and knowing that this patch was going to be bad I set up some tests. Before patch I dueled a lv 50 warrior 5 times, a lvl 50 savage 5 times, a lvl 50 thane 5 times and a lvl 50 skald 5 times everyone of these guys was in my guild and no RAs were used like IP or purge. These were the results.<br>
(AXE)Warrior beat me 3 times.<br>
(Hammer)Thane beat me 3 times.<br>
(H2H)Savage beat me once.<br>
(AXE)Skald beat me 2 times.<br>
<br>
Now before you guys fly off the handle about RR and armor and such we were all RR3L2 - RR3L6 and each one of us had fully SCed armor with max resists across the board. <br>
Now here is after the patch came out live.<br>
Warrior beat me 5 times<br>
Thane beat me 4 times<br>
Savage beat me twice<br>
Skald beat me 4 times<br>
<br>
before patch DBLFST was hitting for about + 100-170<br>
after patch DBLFST was hitting for +45-89<br>
After playing some PVE also I was ready to park my fat troll ass at the forge and just craft......... but wait I have a free respecc and I had a respec stone also. So i figured what the hell I might as well have some fun. so I did the unthinkable I respecced 50 sword 50 parry 28 left axe.<br>
Now why do you ask sword??? how does a 3 pary parry chain sound and a lvl 50 rear style. I will swear to this right now my damage wasnt what it was with a MP DS and a MP wba but it is damn close. so I called up my guildes again and we tried the duels again.<br>
Warrior beat me 4 times ( one of the battles was down to about 15 hps each)<br>
Thane beat me 3 times (parried about 15 attacks <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
Savage beat me twice.<br>
Skald beat me twice( cant hurt what u cant hit)<br>
To sum all this rambling up I am very happy with mt 50 sword 50 parry spec now we can actually do some decent damage and parry a crap load now.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showPrevMessage?topicID=104.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showNextMessage?topicID=104.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=104.topic&index=7><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/professional/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.emailToFriend?topicID=104.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.threadControl?topicID=104.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/slate/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=104.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub79.ezboard.com/flighttanksofdaocfrm3.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=104.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub79.ezboard.com/BBS